Summary
The program uses the Caesar Cipher algorithm.
Users can choose to encrypt or decrypt a message.
It supports both uppercase and lowercase letters.
Non-alphabetic characters (spaces, numbers, punctuation) remain unchanged.
The shift value determines how many positions each letter moves in the alphabet.

Features:

Encrypts text using a user-defined shift value.
Decrypts the encrypted text back to its original form.
Supports both uppercase and lowercase letters.
Preserves spaces, numbers, and special characters.
